				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: bellow of chaos?<a name="67653"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 1:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can't always use your dots. Sometimes, though I will admit only recently, mobs are designed with high resistance to dots but not direct damage, or more generally have high FR/CR/PR/DR but not so much MR. Alternatively, it can be used for some extra dps if you'd care to drop one buffsong instead of two. Finally, it stacks with other bards, where as only one bard can do dots. 
<br />

<br />
Not that most guilds have enough bards that dot stacking is an issue. I know mine haven't, except on ranged damage fights like Fennin. Of course, Bellow is useless on those kinds of fights, because its range is too short to be comfortable. I experimented with its precursor once on Fennin, and a 100 range will invariably put you in PBAE range, unless the guild corners him (and few do).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
