				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: bellow of chaos?<a name="67686"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 11:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I freely admit I seldom use Saryrn's Scream of Pain but I have a question:
<br />

<br />
The old level 12 DD, Brusco's, did NOT interrupt NPC casters.  It did ostensibly have a movement component, but it never interrupted any NPC - I tested that extensively when I was a young bard hanging around in Oasis of Marr.  In PvP, it was devastating -- almost always interrupted casting, medding, bandaging, etc.  Now, mechanically speaking, Saryrn's and this new DD seem to be described in the same terms.
<br />

<br />
Can someone verify that they really DO interrupt NPC casters?  Sony never allowed that on the earlier versions, only let it affect Player Character casters.  I would like someone to verify, preferably with a nice screenshot, that this new DD really does have the power to do what the BB AA ability does not -- interrupt a high level NPC caster.</span></td>
