				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: bellow of chaos?<a name="67715"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 3:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Brusco's Boastful Bellow ONLY interrupts for PvP -- that much I have verified for certain.  This goes back about 3 years -- at that time people were just sure that the level 12 bellow interrupted NPC casters because of the knockback.  It does not and were pretty much able to prove it with a lot of practice so the knockback aspect does not guarantee you're going to interrupt an NPC.  Hand of the Gods, the proc on cleric hammers, used to have a knockback with absolutely zero stun/interrupt capability.  I think they have removed the knockback from the cleric hammer.  I came to the conclusion a long time ago that knockback alone has no effect on NPC casting - only player characters.  About the only way to verify it would be to fight a caster mob that does low damage so you can keep going for awhile, do nothing but cast bellow and see if you get an interrupt.  I know Brusco's does not.  I never really tested Saryrn's and I don't have the new one.</span></td>
